---
---

<section class="border-t border-rule py-20 sm:py-28 px-6 fade-in">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">/ The Principal</p>
    <h2 class="display text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[1.05] mb-3 text-bone" style="font-weight: 500;">
      Platte F. <span class="display-italic" style="font-weight: 500;">Clark</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-bone-mute mb-14">
      Principal · Straw Dogs LLC · WGA Member
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 lg:gap-14">
      <!-- Photo + Podcast -->
      <div class="md:col-span-1 space-y-9">
        <figure>
          <div class="surface rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
            <img
              src="/images/platte-headshot.jpg"
              alt="Platte F. Clark"
              class="w-full aspect-[3/4] object-cover"
              style="filter: contrast(1.05) saturate(0.95);"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <figcaption class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-bone-mute mt-3">
            Premiere · Best Christmas Pageant Ever<br/>Lionsgate, 2024
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <div class="surface rounded-sm p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-copper"></span>
            <p class="mono-label">On the Air / Co-Hosted</p>
          </div>
          <h3 class="display text-2xl mb-3 text-bone" style="font-weight: 500;">The Author Unknown Podcast</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-bone-soft leading-relaxed mb-5">
            The science and psychology of why some stories create change&mdash;conversations
            with neuroscientists, AI researchers, behaviorists, and master storytellers on
            the mechanics of belief.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://authorunknown.fm"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.14em] uppercase text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-1.5"
          >
            authorunknown.fm
            <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 3L9 9M9 3v6H3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="square"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-5 text-bone-soft leading-relaxed text-[1.05rem]">
        <p>
          Platte F. Clark is the principal of Straw Dogs LLC. He is the credited writer on the
          2024 Lionsgate feature <em class="copper not-italic font-medium">The Best Christmas Pageant Ever</em> (92% Critics, 97%
          Audiences), the novelist behind the <em class="copper not-italic font-medium">Bad Unicorn</em> trilogy at Aladdin / Simon &amp;
          Schuster (250,000+ copies), and the ghostwriter behind nearly thirty nonfiction titles
          for executives, founders, and category-defining experts&mdash;including multiple
          FranklinCovey co-authorship credits with the firm's senior leadership.
        </p>
        <p>
          His work outside the page shapes what his work on the page does. Before ghostwriting
          full-time, Clark built behavioral curriculum for FranklinCovey, CrucialLearning, and
          ZengerFolkman, and served as Chief Learning Officer at a partner company with Tony
          Robbins focused on B-to-B training. That instructional-design background is the engine
          under the architecture: he writes books that change how the reader behaves after they
          close the cover.
        </p>
        <p>
          Clark is currently authoring <em class="copper not-italic font-medium">Author Unknown: Why Some Stories Change People and Most
          Don't</em> (forthcoming, Grey + Miller Agency), a working theory of narrative as
          behavior-change technology.
        </p>
        <p>
          He is a WGA member, holds a B.S. in Philosophy (cum laude&mdash;the BS unintentional)
          and an M.S. in English / Instructional Technology, and lives in American Fork, Utah.
        </p>

        <div class="pt-3">
          <a
            href="https://platteclark.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.14em] uppercase text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-1.5"
          >
            platteclark.com
            <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 3L9 9M9 3v6H3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="square"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
